&lt;p&gt;The Breiman Example and the meaning of the columns are described &lt;a href=&quot;http://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-122?focusedCommentId=12718777&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#action_12718777&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;here &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mean RI num nodes: mean number of nodes in the forest built using Random Selection&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mean SI num nodes: mean number of nodes in the forest built using Single-Input Selection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;the variations in the error rates are due (I hope) to the randomness in the process. The built times are relative (but note that I&apos;m running Ubuntu inside a VirtualBox). and we can see that the modification effectively reduces the number of nodes in the &quot;poker&quot; dataset.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
